  "prompt": "How much is a kidney transplant in the USA?",
  "response": "The cost of a kidney transplant in the USA can vary widely depending on several factors, including the hospital, geographic location, and whether or not the patient has health insurance. On average, the cost can range from $250,000 to $400,000. This amount typically includes the surgery itself, as well as pre-transplant evaluations and post-transplant care.\n\nHere's a rough breakdown of the costs involved:\n\n1. **Pre-transplant evaluation and testing:** $10,000 to $20,000\n2. **Surgery and hospital stay:** $150,000 to $250,000\n3. **Post-transplant medications and follow-up care:** $20,000 to $30,000 in the first year, with ongoing costs of $12,000 to $15,000 annually.\n\nIt's important to note that many insurance plans, including Medicare and Medicaid, cover a significant portion of these costs. However, out-of-pocket expenses can still be substantial.\n\nIf you or someone you know is considering a kidney transplant, it's crucial to consult with healthcare providers and insurance representatives to get a more accurate estimate tailored to your specific situation.",
